    <label>pirate (Golden Age)</label>
    <description>Yo ho, yo ho! Despite them having not existed for almost four thousand years, various cultures and societies have long admired the freedom and barbarity of maritime pirates. In contrast to the usual space pirates, these Pirate Crews structure themselves on the Old Earth gangs of swashbuckling seafarers during the ancient Golden Age of Piracy. Old Earth's Golden Age of Piracy lasted approximately eighty years and encompassed great naval feats and battles between the law and the outlaw. This culture continues to carry the traditions of those pirates, albeit influenced by Old Earth pop culture.</description>
